    <text>
        <body>
            <head>211. Telegram From Secretary of State <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu"
                    >Vance</persName> in Switzerland to the Embassy in Morocco<note n="1"
                    place="foot" type="source" xml:id="d211fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                    Security Affairs, Staff Material, Middle East, Subject File, Box 1, Algeria:
                    2–12/77. Confidential; Immediate; <gloss target="#t_Exdis_1">Exdis</gloss>. Sent
                    for information Immediate to the Department of State. Sent for information
                    Priority to <gloss target="#t_USUN_1">USUN</gloss>, Algiers, Madrid, and
                    Nouakchott. Printed from a copy that was received in the White House Situation
                    Room. <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu">Vance</persName> was in Geneva to
                    meet with <persName corresp="recDnAZMmGID4lGnZ">Gromyko</persName> to discuss
                        <rs type="agreement-or-mandate" corresp="recF3SBVeQQW0d1aM">SALT</rs> and
                    the <placeName corresp="recJAi0OpNdSuYev5">Middle East</placeName>.</note>
            </head>
            <opener>
                <dateline rendition="#right">
                    <placeName>Geneva</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1977-05-20T16:05:00+00:00">May 20, 1977, 1605Z</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Secto 4127. Subj: Secretary’s Meeting With <persName corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq"
                    >Waldheim</persName>: <placeName corresp="recGZlEaPYk6Kf3qK">Sahara</placeName>
                Problem.</p>
            <p>1. During working breakfast May 19 with the Secretary, <gloss target="#t_UN_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recakWMbLwDF9eCZ8">UN</orgName>
                </gloss> Secy General <persName corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq">Waldheim</persName> said
                he wanted to bring the Secretary up to date on the following recent developments
                with respect to the <placeName corresp="recGZlEaPYk6Kf3qK">Sahara</placeName> and to
                seek his assistance.</p>
            <p>2. <persName corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq">Waldheim</persName> said that when he was
                recently in <placeName corresp="recXEA0LEpEd93tFt">Saudi Arabia</placeName>, he had
                met with <placeName corresp="recB0DySeLFQaTlMd">Algerian</placeName> Foreign
                Minister <persName corresp="recZPQuJcpaVQkUHt">Bouteflika</persName>, who had asked
                for his help in finding a face-saving formula<note n="2" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d211fn2">An unknown hand underlined “face-saving formula.”</note> for
                Algiers. Subsequently, when he was in Maputo, he had been approached by an emissary
                of <persName corresp="recFHGSIQJfkdnNvO">Boumediene</persName>’s (phonetic spelling
                Sahnoun) with a further request for his assistance.</p>
            <p>3. One idea that had occurred to him, <persName corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq"
                    >Waldheim</persName> said, was the autonomy for the <placeName
                    corresp="recGZlEaPYk6Kf3qK">Sahara</placeName>. With both the <gloss
                    target="#t_OAU_1">
                    <orgName corresp="reclJ1I8Ix3s26TFu">OAU</orgName>
                </gloss> and <gloss target="#t_UN_1">
                    <orgName corresp="recakWMbLwDF9eCZ8">UN</orgName>
                </gloss> divided on this subject, however, King <persName
                    corresp="rec8m8MetQlvwXVeh">Hassan</persName> felt in a strong position and
                    <persName corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq">Waldheim</persName> doubted that he was
                ready for a face-saving solution. He was nevertheless in touch with a Moroccan
                representative in Geneva to explore whether any new approach to this problem was
                possible. The Algerians hoped for a solution before the African summit in <placeName
                    corresp="recr6k8TVXxEPlyr5">Gabon</placeName> in July and were urging him to
                visit the area. <persName corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq">Waldheim</persName> said he
                wanted first, however, to see whether <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl"
                    >Morocco</placeName> was ready for any kind of face-saving procedure such as,
                for example, a process of consultations with Saharoui leaders. He had also discussed
                this problem with Sadruddin Aga Khan, who is carrying out census of Saharouis in
                    <placeName corresp="recB0DySeLFQaTlMd">Algeria</placeName>.</p>
            <p>4. <persName corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq">Waldheim</persName> said that <persName
                    corresp="recFHGSIQJfkdnNvO">Boumediene</persName>’s emissary had told him the
                Moroccans were massing troops on the <placeName corresp="recB0DySeLFQaTlMd"
                    >Algerian</placeName> border. According to Sadruddin Khan, there was no doubt
                the Algerians are supporting the <pb facs="0529" n="508" xml:id="pg_508"/>
                <orgName corresp="recejMOrt8OMiixBL">Polisario</orgName>,<note n="3" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d211fn3">For a detailed report on the <orgName
                        corresp="recejMOrt8OMiixBL">Polisario Front</orgName>, see <ref
                        target="#d221">Document 221</ref>.</note> and he is concerned about a
                possible <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">Moroccan</placeName> preemptive
                strike across the border against Tindouf.</p>
            <p>5. The Secretary said we have good relations with <persName
                    corresp="rec8m8MetQlvwXVeh">Hassan</persName> and could use our good offices in
                support of the Secretary General.<note n="4" place="foot" xml:id="d211fn4">An
                    unknown hand highlighted this sentence.</note>
                <persName corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq">Waldheim</persName> said we could tell
                    <persName corresp="rec8m8MetQlvwXVeh">Hassan</persName> of the approach to him
                by <persName corresp="recFHGSIQJfkdnNvO">Boumediene</persName>’s emissary in Maputo,
                who had said that <placeName corresp="recB0DySeLFQaTlMd">Algeria</placeName> is
                worried about the situation and has asked the Secretary General to take an
                initiative which could contribute to a solution of the problem.</p>
            <p>6. <persName corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq">Waldheim</persName> said he was cautious
                about again involving himself in the Saharan situation after his last experience.
                King <persName corresp="rec8m8MetQlvwXVeh">Hassan</persName> takes the position that
                the problem has been solved and that the <rs type="topic"
                    corresp="rec3vXdKC3r5GaUzW">self-determination</rs> requirement was fulfilled
                through his consultation with the Saharoui Assembly. Neither <placeName
                    corresp="recfnWmyxHI2lF8xT">Spain</placeName> nor <placeName
                    corresp="recB0DySeLFQaTlMd">Algeria</placeName> accepts this, however, pointing
                out that <persName corresp="rec8m8MetQlvwXVeh">Hassan</persName> only consulted a
                rump assembly consisting of Moroccan stooges. They did not agree that this fulfilled
                    <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">Morocco</placeName>’s obligation under
                the <placeName corresp="recLpHNCu4qy8XTDl">Moroccan</placeName>-<placeName
                    corresp="rec8AtlHhYG0QfwTi">Mauritanian</placeName>-<placeName
                    corresp="recfnWmyxHI2lF8xT">Spanish</placeName> agreement.<note n="5"
                    place="foot" xml:id="d211fn5">Reference is to the 1975 Morocco Accords; see <ref
                        target="#d31fn5">footnote 5, Document 31</ref>.</note> What is needed,
                    <persName corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq">Waldheim</persName> concluded, is a
                face-saving formula for the Algerians.</p>
            <p>7. Before deciding how to proceed in support of <persName corresp="recO0C3IMJcbbKRcq"
                    >Waldheim</persName>’s request for help, we would like Rabat’s analysis and
                recommendations. We would also welcome any comments that info addressees may
                have.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>
                    <persName corresp="recRM4qiy2MVhNDPu">
                        <hi rendition="simple_bold">Vance</hi>
                    </persName>
                </signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
